On January 16, 1989, Patrick Edward Purdy, 24, fired an AK-47 into a playground at 
Stockton, California's Cleveland Elementary School, which he had attended. He killed 
five children and wounded 30, then killed himself. The slain children were Southeast 
Asian. Purdy had drifted around the country searching for work and had a long criminal 
record.</SUM>
